article.headline: Pritchard puts up 23 as Central Michigan knocks off Western Michigan 62-55
article.description: — Anthony Pritchard had 23 points in Central Michigan's 62-55 win against Western Michigan on Saturday.
article.linkText: Pritchard puts up 23 as Central Michigan knocks off Western Michigan 62-55
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. -- — Anthony Pritchard had 23 points in Central Michigan's 62-55 win against Western Michigan on Saturday. Pritchard added eight rebounds, six assists, and three steals for the Chippewas (11-9, 6-2 Mid-American Conference). Markus Harding scored 15 points while going 6 of 11 and 3 of 3 from the free throw line. Derrick Butler had eight points and was 3 of 8 shooting (2 for 4 from 3-point range). The Broncos (8-12, 5-3) were led by Seth Hubbard, who recorded 16 points. Western Michigan also got 10 points and 12 rebounds from Owen Lobsinger. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
